-- Bank of America Names Steinemann, Zhang as Industrials Co-Heads
-- B y   C a t h y   C h a n
-- 2012-06-07T02:58:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/bank-of-america-names-steinemann-zhang-as-industrials-co-heads.html
Bank of America Corp.  named Patrick Steinemann and Richard Zhang as co-heads of Asia industrials
investment banking, according to an internal memo obtained by
Bloomberg News.  Zhang was hired from  Citigroup Inc. (C) , where he was head of
Greater China metals and mining investment banking, according to
the document. He began his career at Merrill Lynch & Co. as an
associate, it said. Mark Tsang, a Hong Kong-based spokesman for
Charlotte, North Carolina-based Bank of America, confirmed the
contents of the memo.  Steinemann has been with Merrill Lynch, which was acquired
by Bank of America in 2009, since 1998 and was most recently
covering the capital goods and automotive sectors in the Asia-
Pacific region, according to the memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cathy Chan in  Hong Kong  at 
